<TITLE> US's Rice to meet Russian rights activists </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOSCOW, Oct 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice is to have a breakfast meeting with Russian human rights activists, highlighting Washington's concerns about Russia's rights record, one of the invitees said on Wednesday. Tatyana Lokshina, head of the Demos non-governmental group which campaigns against rights abuses in Chechnya, said she and about 10 other activists had been invited to meet Rice on Saturday, Oct. 13, during a visit to Moscow. "One of my key topics is the situation in Chechnya and I will definitely raise it," Lokshina told Reuters. "It is very important that the United States has a very well thought out stand towards Russia, together with the European Union. If the EU and United States deliver the same messages, it would be more effective." The State Department has not published Rice's schedule for the visit to Russia. She is travelling with Defense Secretary Robert Gates for talks that are due to focus on the planned U.S. missile defence shield in eastern Europe, which Moscow opposes. The United States and other Western states say they are concerned that Russia under President Vladimir Putin is backtracking on democratic freedoms and civil rights. Putin has denied this. He has accused foreign governments of exploiting the human rights issue as a pretext to interfere in Russia's domestic affai
